wiki.content: “Woman’s World” is a song by American recording artist Cher, and is the lead single for her upcoming twenty-sixth studio album “Closer To the Truth”, due to be released in September of 2013. “Woman's World” is written by Matt Morris, Paul Oakenfold and Anthony Crawford, while production was handled by Oakenfold. Musically, the song is a dance-influenced song that contains elements of europop and house music. Lyrically, the song is a female empowerment anthem in which Cher exclaims that she is "strong enough to rise above" because "this is a woman's world". On November 22, 2012 the "Woman's World" was streamed on Cher's official website as a Thanksgiving treat for her fans.
